</p>
<p>162. The Special Rapporteur refers again to Human Rights Council resolution 15/21, and 
in particular operative paragraph 1 that &#8220;[c]alls upon States to respect and fully protect the 
</p>
<p>rights of all individuals to assemble peacefully and associate freely, including in the context 
of elections, and including persons espousing minority or dissenting views or beliefs, 
human rights defenders, trade unionists and others, including migrants, seeking to exercise 
or to promote these rights, and to take all necessary measures to ensure that any restrictions 
on the free exercise of the rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association are in 
accordance with their obligations under international human rights law&#8221;. </p>

<p><b>A/HRC/20/27/Add.3 
</b></p>
<p><b>24  
</b></p>
